Cäcilie Auguste (Olga) "Ольга Фёдоровна" Romanova formerly Sachsen-Coburg-Saalfeld aka von Baden

Born 20 Sep 1839 in Karlsruhe, Großherzogtum Baden, Deutscher Bund

Ancestors

Wife of Михаи́л Никола́евич Рома́нов — married 28 Aug 1857 in Санкт-Петербург, Российская империя

Descendants

Died 13 Apr 1891 at age 51 in Харків, Російська імперія

Profile last modified 16 May 2023 | Created 2 May 2015

This page has been accessed 1,124 times.

Olga (Sachsen-Coburg-Saalfeld) Romanova was a member of aristocracy in Europe.

Join: European Royals and Aristocrats Project

Discuss: euroaristo

Biography

Princess Cäcilie Auguste of Baden, was the youngest daughter of Grand Duke Leopold of Baden and Sophie Wilhelmine of Sweden. She married Grand Duke Michael Nikolaievich of Russia, the youngest son of Tsar Nicholas I of Russia, on 28 August 1857 at the Chapel of the Winter Palace in Saint Petersburg. She took the name Olga Feodorovna (Russian: Ольга Фёдоровна) upon conversion to the Orthodox faith[1].

She died at Kharkhov on 12 April 1891 after suffering a heart attack while travelling to Crimea on train[1]

Her alleged biological father was Moritz von Haber, a Karlsruhe banker of Jewish origin.
